Problem Statement 2 – Orders Management
     An online store wants to track orders and customers.
     Some customers may not have placed any order.
     Some orders may exist without a valid customer (guest checkout).


Focused Exercises

1. List all orders with customer names (INNER JOIN).
2. Show all orders including guest orders (customer_id = NULL).
3. Show all customers including those with no orders.
4. Find total number of orders per customer.
5. Find total amount spent per customer.

6. Show customers who haven’t placed any orders.
7. Show orders above 20,000 in value.
8. Find the average order amount.
9. Show the maximum order amount per customer.
10. Show the latest order date for each customer.
